other_tests.findings: Multiple sebaceous glands within the superficial papillary dermis. Increased mucin and increased numbers of ectatic vessels. Areas of extramedullary hematopoiesis, including nucleated red cells and myeloid precursors, were seen throughout the mass. Immature adipose tissue and lipoblasts were identified.
other_tests.changes_over_time: At 4 months, immature adipose and hematopoietic elements, as well as vascular changes, had resolved.
